rComments: hardest psych course ive taken, & i got a 4.0 in psy202 (stats). way too much information to study so i ran out of time studying and didnt get to memorize my notes which is a big deal since the course is memorization based. the material isnt hard to understand but the course is hard because of all the stuff u need to know. tests 135 marks exam 150!
Her tests are very tricky. The short answer questions are always a surprise no matter how much you study and it's unclear what she expects from test answers. She reads right off the slides.
Read off the slides. Contributed very little of her own insight. Midterms were difficult, and expects you to memorize small, random details.
She reads from the slides, word for word. Focuses mostly on rats and their sexual behaviors. Her tests have random questions. She shows no interest in the material.

Don't know what all the fuss is about. Yes she's smart, nice & approachable but to be honest the tests were pure memorization. She actually took a small diagram from one of the homework articles and made it worth 10 marks on the test which she later took out because everyone failed it. Know everything for the tests is really an understatement.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Classes can seem a little boring but she does really try to make them interesting. She may seem a little intimidating from first glance and expects you to be knowing your stuff, but if you need ANY clarification especially on a one-on-one basis, she is AMAZING! Tests come mainly from lectures but don't rule out textbook! Fantastic prof!

Prof Ahkbari is honestly amazing. She is extremely approachable and also gives many personal examples which I found to be extremely beneficial. She is also humorous, and did I mention she is a hottie. I honestly loved her, I really hope that one day she will achieve tenure. I received a 4.0 in her class, as a result of thorough efforts! Amazing!
hated her class, she is not helpful at all and marks word by word and thats rediculous
No point being in her class, everything you can learn yourself in lecture. Seriously.

This professor is probably one of the best you'll get during your undergrad at UofT. Tests and exam are fair but can be tricky if you don't  have an interest in the subject. Don't have to attend class as the lecture slides are very clear and straight forward, but you'd really be missing out on a great lecture experience. And yes, she is hot.

Very good lecturer. She doesnt bore the class especially with her great sense of humour. She comes prepared and knows the information as well. The tests were easy except for the diagrams which were all somewhat tricky. The best part is she always finishes the class early (about30-45 mins every lecture).

Awesome Prof. One of the most down to earth and intelligent professors out of all UofT departments. Very enthusiastic with her research, and is always willing to share stories with her students. Genuinely cares for the well being, success. and abilities of her undergrads. She looks like she could a be a student with how young and pretty she is.

she's a great prof. I honestly wasnt looking forward to this class because there was a poster presentation, but it was much better than I expected, very casual, no pressure. Annnd.. she's really nice as well. Tests are extremely fair (almost easy, lets hope the exam will be the same)

She is honestly one of the best profs I've had in the Psychology department.  She presents current and extremely interesting research relevant to what she's teaching.  Her tests are extremely fair.  She also really cares about her students doing well, not only in her course but in further pursuits in academia.  Overall stellar teacher & person.

If you take psy290 with her in summer, DONT bother buying the tb. Everything on the tests is STRAIGHT from the lectures. All you have to do is memorize/understand the lecture slides and you're guaranteed a 4.0.

She's an AMAZING prof, really tries to help/make it interesting, but the material itself has its dull moments. The tests are fair, but there is a lot of material which can make it rather difficult. Be prepared to do a ton of reading from both the slides and textbook, and lots of memorizing!

Got a 4.0 but it comes with hard work and studying! Might be tough if you don't have a bio background and if you can't stand sitting 3 hours in class learning about neurons! Other than that, USE the textbook, READ the lectures, and ASK for help. She is so sweet and genuinely wants her students to do well :). Be prepared for a 40% paper too!
